All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Cell
Cell holds information of each cell on the board including the images.
Direction
Direction This enum defines a direction.
Domain
Domain class - runs game logic.
Draw
Draw gets a gamestate from domain and then returns a JPanel.
Enemy
Enemy this class defines an enemy's position, direction and speed
Entry<K,V>
An Entry class representing a key-value pair for working with LHander to parse the level name and level file string.
ExplanationFrame
A frame that displays instructions on how to play the Chaps Challenge game.
Game
The central class for the "Chips Challenge" game that represents the game window.
KeyHandler
Handles keyboard input for controlling the game and managing game state.
Level
Level this class defines a 2d array of cells which can be manipulated with the method getTiles.
LevelHandler
Manages and controls gameplay for a specific game level, handling user input, game state updates, and timers.
LHander
Enum representing different game levels and their filename.
Load
This class is designed to load player information, level or past game info from JSON format.
Main
The main class that serves as the entry point for the Chaps Challenge game application.
Player
Player This is a simple class which stores the player's inventory, position, and contains a method for checking this information.
Recorder
Recorder class contains necessary methods for App to use to save and load replay files
RecorderHelper
RecorderHelper class contains necessary methods for Recorder class to use to save and load replay files
RecorderTest
 
ReplayGame
The ReplayGame class represents the panel for replaying a game using recorder.
Saver
This class is designed to Save the current map and player information to JSON format.
SoundPlayer
Soundplayer This is a simple class for playing sounds stored in the .wav format
testPersistency
This class is responsible for testing the persistancy package.
TestPersistency
